trends: There have been 17 other sightings in Flushing
There was one other sighting in Flushing on or around June 18th 2013
divs: Sighting DetailsADDITIONAL INFO FOR THIS CASE: The trees in question that the "snake-like" rope-light landed on (and subsequently burst into what could be described as "intense fireworks"?), has apparent burned-looking, shriveled up leaves on it where this light landed. It literally appears that these leaves were baked on the limb. In addition, there is a broken branch hanging down in the middle of these dead-looking leaves. The MUFON investigator called, and was informed of this immediately after the sighting, and we were asked to take photos of the tree. Photos have been taken, but without a professional camera, it really doesn't do it justice. If anyone at MUFON is interested in investigating it further, we would still be very interested in finding out what in the world.....(or not) it was. Leaves are falling fast, however..............Not included crappy photos taken with cell phone....as it is very difficult to see. This is one of those "you have to see it to believe it" things..........
